Former Arsenal star, Paul Merson, has predicted the outcomes of Premier League matchday 29 fixtures. Manchester United will host Tottenham Hotspur on Saturday evening at Old Trafford, while Chelsea will face Newcastle United at Stamford Bridge on Sunday. Liverpool will face Brighton in an away Premier League tie on Saturday afternoon and Arsenal will host Leicester City on Sunday evening at Emirates. Providing his predictions, Merson was quoted by Sportskeeda as saying: Brighton & Hove Albion 0-3 Liverpool Brentford 2-1 Burnley Manchester United 2-1 Tottenham Hotspur Chelsea 2-0 Newcastle United Leeds United 1-1 Norwich City Everton 1-2 Wolverhampton Wanderers West Ham United 1-2 Aston Villa Southampton 3-0 Watford Arsenal 3-1 Leicester City Crystal Palace 2-1 Manchester City